Unnamed: 2: 40 Years Proudly Serving Newcomers In Toronto

VWAT (Vietnamese Women's Association of Toronto) is a non-profit organization that has been helping refugee and immigrant families integrate into Canadian society since 1982. We provide services for newcomers, youth, and seniors in their communities, with a focus on helping Vietnamese newcomers. We also focus on preserving Vietnamese heritage through annual cultural festivals
Wholesome Excellence Care Accountability Inclusion Respect Equity

VWAT Family Services is located in Toronto, also known as Tkaronto, along Garrison Creek south of Davenport Road, part of the Carrying Place. Our organization acknowledges that we are on the land of many nations including the Mississaugas of the Credit, the Anishnabeg, the Haudenosaunee, the Chippewa and Wendat peoples. Tkaronto is now home to many diverse First Nations, Inuit and Métis peoples. Our location is covered by Treaty 13. We respectfully thank these Nations and people for stewarding this land.
